<h4 id="accrued-lease-payment" sourcefile="finance/asset-leasing/asset-leasing-quick-start.md" sourcestartlinenumber="150">Accrued lease payment</h4>
<p sourcefile="finance/asset-leasing/asset-leasing-quick-start.md" sourcestartlinenumber="151">An accrued lease payment is recognized as a lease future payment thatâ€™s due to process as a payment transaction from the bank or cash accounts. The lease payment due decreases the lease liability by debiting the lease liability account against whether a vendor subledger in case of the lessor is defined as a vendor, or posting the credit side to a notes payable ledger account then the payment will be executed against either vendor or notes payable.</p>
